    "narrative": "The Austin Waves open the 2026 campaign with a heavy offensive leaning today, headlined by **Gunnar Henderson** and **Kyle Tucker**. **Gunnar Henderson** commands our highest efficiency score of 81.88, bolstered by a massive 16% park factor and the premium leadoff spot against R. Nelson, while **Kyle Tucker** (72.86) remains an auto-start despite facing a lefty, as his elite xwOBA and favorable wind conditions outweigh the platoon disadvantage. We are also monitoring **Luis Robert Jr.** (62.20) closely; while he faces a tough assignment in the sub-3.00 xERA Wrobleski, his elite speed profile combined with the pitcher\u2019s slow delivery suggests a high probability of a stolen base\u2014our most coveted category\u2014making him a critical asset despite the matchup friction.\n\nDeciding the final bench spots required navigating several marginal scores, specifically with **Nasim Nunez**, who fell just short of our 40.0 floor at 38.00. While **Nasim Nunez** provides necessary speed, the combination of a difficult matchup against Skenes and an elite-tier catcher holding a 1.89s pop time neutralized his stolen base upside, forcing him to the bench in favor of more stable production from the likes of **Josh Lowe** and **Andy Pages**. We are currently navigating a thin bench with **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** and **Jackson Merrill** idle today, and **Jordan Westburg** remains sidelined on the IL, leaving little margin for error if our starters encounter early-game weather delays or mid-game substitutions. Proceed with caution against the Skenes start for **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.**, as the 19% SP skill penalty makes his 53.13 score more tenuous than the raw number suggests.",
